The '''People's Inquest''' was a grassroots populist [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]-accountability watch-group active before and during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

==History==
They supported [[Jonava Billane]] in the [["Baby Ludi" custody case|Case of "Baby Ludi"]]. [[Thrynka Padaunete]] was [[President/Legends|president]] of the People's Inquest. They were known for their multiple petitions and marches on the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]]. In one particular march, several [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]] were overwhelmed and were unable to quell the angry group. [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Plo Koon/Legends|Plo Koon]] easily dispatched the disruptive mob using a Jedi [[Mind trick/Legends|mind trick]].

In the wake of [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]], the People's Inquest aided the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] by compiling a list of all known Jedi that were still at large, along with information on other Force-using sects.

